x4freetext: The resonance fit was performed with the Bayesian
code SAMMY in the formalism of the multilevel
Breit-Wigner formula. The resolution function of the
neutron beam, Doppler broadening due to the thermal
motion of the target nuclei, the finite size of the s
ample in single scattering, self-shielding effects were
taken into account in the analysis.
The energy and fission width of the resonances were
left free during the fit, gamma and neutron widths were
kept fixed to the initial values.
